@page "/learn/export"
@layout MacroSutra.Web.Components.Layout.LandingLayout

<PageTitle>MacroSutra - Trade Export Guide</PageTitle>

<section class="landing-section">
    <div class="landing-container">
        <h1>Trade Export</h1>
        <p>Export your trade history to CSV or PDF for record-keeping, tax preparation, or offline analysis.</p>

        <h2 id="csv" class="mt-4">CSV Export</h2>
        <p>CSV exports include the following columns for every trade in your account:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Date</strong> &mdash; Trade creation timestamp (UTC).</li>
            <li><strong>Symbol</strong> &mdash; The ticker symbol traded.</li>
            <li><strong>Side</strong> &mdash; Buy or Sell.</li>
            <li><strong>Type</strong> &mdash; Order type (Market, Limit, Stop, etc.).</li>
            <li><strong>Qty</strong> &mdash; Requested quantity.</li>
            <li><strong>FilledQty</strong> &mdash; Quantity actually filled.</li>
            <li><strong>FilledPrice</strong> &mdash; Average fill price.</li>
            <li><strong>Status</strong> &mdash; Current order status (Filled, Submitted, Cancelled, etc.).</li>
            <li><strong>StrategyId</strong> &mdash; The strategy that triggered the trade, if any.</li>
            <li><strong>Notes</strong> &mdash; Any notes or alert text associated with the trade.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To export from the UI, navigate to <strong>Trading &rarr; Trades</strong> and click <strong>Export CSV</strong>. The file downloads immediately to your browser.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-3">SDK Export</h3>
<pre><code>var csvBytes = await client.Trades.ExportCsvAsync();
File.WriteAllBytes("trades.csv", csvBytes);</code></pre>

        <h2 id="pdf" class="mt-4">PDF Export</h2>
        <p>PDF exports generate a formatted trade report with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>A header with report title and generation timestamp.</li>
            <li>A table of all trades with Date, Symbol, Side, Type, Qty, Filled Price, and Status columns.</li>
            <li>Page numbers in the footer.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Click <strong>Export PDF</strong> on the Trades page to download. The PDF uses landscape A4 format for readability.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-3">SDK Export</h3>
<pre><code>var pdfBytes = await client.Trades.ExportPdfAsync();
File.WriteAllBytes("trades.pdf", pdfBytes);</code></pre>

        <h2 id="api" class="mt-4">API Endpoint</h2>
        <p>Both formats are available via a single endpoint:</p>
<pre><code>GET /api/trades/export?format=csv
GET /api/trades/export?format=pdf</code></pre>
        <p>Optional query parameters: <code>symbol</code> and <code>strategyId</code> to filter the exported trades.</p>

        <p class="mt-4"><a href="/learn">&larr; Back to Learn</a></p>
    </div>
</section>
